{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/2508","id":3695651068,"node_id":"PR_kwDOEHbxG87cRyj8","html_url":"https://github.com/doldecomp/melee/pull/2508","diff_url":"https://github.com/doldecomp/melee/pull/2508.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/doldecomp/melee/pull/2508.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/issues/2508","number":2508,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"lb: implement lb_80019628; improve four lbbgflash functions","user":{"login":"itsgrimetime","id":990274,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk5MDI3NA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/990274?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime","html_url":"https://github.com/itsgrimetime","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/itsgrimetime/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Summary\n\n- **`lb_0192.c`** (`lb_80019628`): adds a C body for the pad-sampling-rate maintenance function called from `lb_80019894`. Snapshots `lb_804329F0.x38`, picks the minimum of `x0[0].x0` / `x0[1].x0` / `OS_TIMER_CLOCK` / `OS_TIMER_CLOCK * 1/60` as the new period, divides by `OS_TIMER_CLOCK/1000` for the ms cap (≤ 11), then updates `PADSetSamplingRate` and reschedules the periodic alarm with `fn_800195FC`.\n- **`lbbgflash.c`** (`fn_8001FC08`): restructures each per-channel saturation block to use branch-local `u8 target` / `f32* cur` locals so MWCC keeps the byte target and the `x10[i]` pointer in r5/r4 across the rising/falling logic.\n- **`lbbgflash.c`** (`lbBgFlash_80020E38`): reorders the squared-component locals (dx2/dy2/dz2 instead of dz2/dx2/dy2) and the sum to match how the original schedules the lfs/fmuls/fadds pipeline.\n- **`lbbgflash.c`** (`fn_8002113C`): routes `&rot` through a `Quaternion* volatile` local so MWCC keeps the inline-substituted asserts at `jobj.h:699/700` in the `Fake_HSD_JObjGetRotation` expansion (previously the compiler proved `&rot` non-null and elided the assert call entirely).\n- **`lbbgflash.c`** (`fn_80020AEC`): expands `parent = jobj ? jobj->parent : NULL;` to an explicit `if/else` so MWCC schedules the non-null case first, matching the bne / b / li sequence the original emits for `parent`.\n\n## Functions matched\n\nNo 100% matches. Five improvements toward the original:\n\n- `lb_80019628`: 0% (no source body — was relying on the asm-only fallback) → **82.58%** fuzzy\n- `fn_8001FC08`: 89.55% → **91.77%** fuzzy\n- `fn_8002113C`: 93.17% → **94.72%** fuzzy\n- `fn_80020AEC`: 88.27% → **88.77%** fuzzy\n- `lbBgFlash_80020E38`: 98.46% → **98.52%** fuzzy\n\n## Files\n\n- `src/melee/lb/lb_0192.c`\n- `src/melee/lb/lbbgflash.c`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `python configure.py && ninja` → green (`build/GALE01/main.dol: OK`)\n- All sibling functions in both TUs unchanged.","created_at":"2026-05-16T21:39:38Z","updated_at":"2026-05-16T22:54:12Z","closed_at":"2026-05-16T22:27:08Z","merged_at":"2026-05-16T22:27:08Z","merge_commit_sha":"9f6156eb562b7d984bb505ef36c505daf49fc1ad","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/2508/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/2508/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doldecomp/melee/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":